  "worklog": "## 2026-03-30 16:39 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] 19h Pre-Session: VWAP Logic Clarified, Regime RANGE 0/6\n\n**Task:** Prepare for 19h session. Verify regime filter and VWAP behavior.\n\n**Finding:**\n1. **Regime: RANGE 0/6** \u2014 consistency 0.62, range 0.76%, trend -0.19%. Choppy action (3\u2191/3\u2193). Will trade \u2705\n\n2. **VWAP misconception corrected:** I initially thought BTC below VWAP would block 19h YES trades. WRONG. The VWAP check aligns with BIAS direction (not bet direction):\n   - Negative bias + price below VWAP \u2192 `(not bullish AND not above_vwap)` = **VWAP AGREES \u2705**\n   - The relaxation at 11h/12h only helps when price is ABOVE VWAP with negative bias (contradictory signals)\n   \n3. **19h conditions:** BTC $67,352, VWAP ~$67,573. Price below VWAP = agrees with negative bias. If bias stays negative, 19h will fire YES trades with VWAP agreement.\n\n4. **19h edge is bias-driven** (per MEMORY: higher |bias| = real signal at established trends). Current bias oscillating -71 to +52 \u2014 high amplitude. If it settles into consistent negative bias at 19h, conditions are good.\n\n**Decision:** No changes needed for 19h. VWAP will agree. Regime is RANGE. Bot will trade normally. The 12:43 VWAP_RELAXED trade was the exception (price above VWAP at 12h London midday), not the rule.\n\n## 2026-03-30 16:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Leaderboard Shift: ETH 82% Short, SOL Flipped Bullish, ETH Position Closed\n\n**Task:** Fresh HL leaderboard scan. Compare positioning changes over 7.5 hours.\n\n**Finding:** Major shifts in top trader positioning:\n\n| Asset | 09:08 UTC | 16:38 UTC | Change |\n|-------|-----------|-----------|--------|\n| BTC | 8L/2S | 6L/3S | Less bullish (-2L) |\n| ETH | 5L/6S | **2L/9S** | **Heavily bearish (+3S)** |\n| SOL | 3L/7S | **7L/4S** | **Flipped bullish (+4L)** |\n\n**ETH: Top traders 82% short while ETH is +3.44%.** Classic smart money fade. Same pattern SOL showed this morning (which reversed \u2014 SOL now bullish